>Project Benefits</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Improved safety, effectiveness and continuity of care through reduced agency / locum usage and stable workforce</li>\r\n	<li>Reduced cost through substantially reduced agency / locum usage</li>\r\n	<li>Full compliance with appropriate clinical and commissioning standards</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Project Lead</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li><strong>Chief Executive Sponsors</strong>: Stephen Eames, The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Medical Directors Sponsors</strong>: Gail Collins - (Surgery), Derek Burke - (Urg and Emer Care)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Project Manager</strong> James Scott, james.scott11@nhs.net</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Commissioner Leads</strong> Dr Tim Moorhead, Phil Mettam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Project Updates</h4>","Children\'s Services","","inherit","closed","open","","250-revision-v1","","","2014-10-06 11:29:27","2014-10-06 11:29:27","","250","http://inch-reform.codio.io:3000/wordpress/250-revision-v1/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("266","1","2014-10-06 11:34:58","2014-10-06 11:34:58","<h1 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Sharing and Adopting Good Practice</h1>\r\n<h3>Workstream Philosophy</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Each Trust has worked hard to improve practice through their own programmes but little of this has been shared. Finding new and innovative ways to improve efficiency has become more difficult but by sharing and adopting these across the Trusts new opportunities will be introduced.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Workstream Aim</h3>\r\nSeeking to standardise where possible on products and services that can be bought more effectively by a large and influential group of Trusts which will introduce discounts not currently enjoyed. These products initially will be those used generically in clinical practice but not pharmaceuticals.\r\n<h2>Projects</h2>\r\nAs well as general projects relating to...\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li>Support Services</li>\r\n	<li>Procurement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Workstream lead</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li><strong>Chief Executive Sponsors</strong>: Simon Morritt, Sheffield Children\'s NHS  Foundation Trust &amp; Andrew Cash Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Project Managers: </strong>Jon Edwards - Jonathan.edwards@supplychain.nhs.uk, Jordan Hope Jordan.Hope@sth.nhs.uk, Benjamin Chico benjamin.chico@rothgen.nhs.uk &amp; Wayne Lugton wayne.lugton@nhs.net</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>For more information</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The workstream groups are just beginning to formulate their plans and further updates will be circulated at regular intervals. For more information, or if you are interested in getting involved, please contact <a style=\"color: #09afad;\" href=\"mailto:janettewatkins@nhs.net\">Janette Watkins (Programme Manager) via email</a> or by telephone on 01709 424 534.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Latest News</h2>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Information on the Working Together programme and specific Workstream groups:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">[display-posts category=\"good-practice\"]</p>","Sharing and Adopting Good Practices","","inherit","closed","open","","16-revision-v1","","","2014-10-06 11:34:58","2014-10-06 11:34:58","","16","http://inch-reform.codio.io:3000/wordpress/16-revision-v1/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("267","1","2014-10-06 11:36:44","2014-10-06 11:36:44","<h1 class=\"sthbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Sharing and Adopting Good Practice</h1>\r\n<h3>Workstream Philosophy</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Each Trust has worked hard to improve practice through their own programmes but little of this has been shared. Finding new and innovative ways to improve efficiency has become more difficult but by sharing and adopting these across the Trusts new opportunities will be introduced.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Workstream Aim</h3>\r\nSeeking to standardise where possible on products and services that can be bought more effectively by a large and influential group of Trusts which will introduce discounts not currently enjoyed. These products initially will be those used generically in clinical practice but not pharmaceuticals.\r\n<h2>Projects</h2>\r\nAs well as general projects relating to...\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li>Support Services</li>\r\n	<li>Procurement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Workstream lead</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li><strong>Chief Executive Sponsors</strong>: Simon Morritt, Sheffield Children\'s NHS  Foundation Trust &amp; Andrew Cash Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Project Managers: </strong>Jon Edwards - Jonathan.edwards@supplychain.nhs.uk, Jordan Hope Jordan.Hope@sth.nhs.uk, Benjamin Chico benjamin.chico@rothgen.nhs.uk &amp; Wayne Lugton wayne.lugton@nhs.net</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>For more information</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The workstream groups are just beginning to formulate their plans and further updates will be circulated at regular intervals. For more information, or if you are interested in getting involved, please contact <a style=\"color: #09afad;\" href=\"mailto:janettewatkins@nhs.net\">Janette Watkins (Programme Manager) via email</a> or by telephone on 01709 424 534.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"sthbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Latest News</h2>\r\n<p>Information on the Working Together programme and specific Workstream groups:</p>\r\n<p>[display-posts category=\"good-practice\"]</p>","Sharing and Adopting Good Practices","","inherit","closed","open","","16-revision-v1","","","2014-10-06 11:36:44","2014-10-06 11:36:44","","16","http://inch-reform.codio.io:3000/wordpress/16-revision-v1/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("268","1","2014-10-06 11:40:46","2014-10-06 11:40:46","<h1 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Support Services</h1>\r\n<h3>Workstream Aim</h3>\r\n<p class=\"lead\">To identify the potential areas where collaboration…</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Project Aims</h3>\r\nTo identify the potential support areas where collaboration\r\nbetween Trusts could bring benefits:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Laboratory services</li>\r\n	<li>Decontamination</li>\r\n	<li>Occupational health</li>\r\n	<li>Payroll, pensions and expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Lease cars</li>\r\n	<li>Legal services</li>\r\n	<li>VAT advice</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Project Benefits</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Economies of scale leading to reduction in costs</li>\r\n	<li>Potential for avoidance of financial investment in equipment</li>\r\n	<li>Maximise equipment utilisation</li>\r\n	<li>Create a pool of expertise</li>\r\n	<li>Improve service resilience</li>\r\n	<li>Process standardisation and simplification</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Project Lead</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li><strong>Chief Executive Sponsors</strong>: Simon Morritt, Sheffield Children\'s NHS Foundation Trust</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Project Managers</strong> Benjamin Chico benjamin.chico@rothgen.nhs.uk &amp; Wayne Lugotn\r\nwayne.lugton@nhs.net</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Project Updates</h4>","Support Services","","publish","closed","open","","support-services","","","2014-10-06 11:40:46","2014-10-06 11:40:46","","16","http://inch-reform.codio.io:3000/wordpress/?page_id=268","0","page","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("269","1","2014-10-06 11:40:46","2014-10-06 11:40:46","<h1 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Support Services</h1>\r\n<h3>Workstream Aim</h3>\r\n<p class=\"lead\">To identify the potential areas where collaboration…</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Project Aims</h3>\r\nTo identify the potential support areas where collaboration\r\nbetween Trusts could bring benefits:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Laboratory services</li>\r\n	<li>Decontamination</li>\r\n	<li>Occupational health</li>\r\n	<li>Payroll, pensions and expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Lease cars</li>\r\n	<li>Legal services</li>\r\n	<li>VAT advice</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Project Benefits</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Economies of scale leading to reduction in costs</li>\r\n	<li>Potential for avoidance of financial investment in equipment</li>\r\n	<li>Maximise equipment utilisation</li>\r\n	<li>Create a pool of expertise</li>\r\n	<li>Improve service resilience</li>\r\n	<li>Process standardisation and simplification</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Project Lead</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li><strong>Chief Executive Sponsors</strong>: Simon Morritt, Sheffield Children\'s NHS Foundation Trust</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Project Managers</strong> Benjamin Chico benjamin.chico@rothgen.nhs.uk &amp; Wayne Lugotn\r\nwayne.lugton@nhs.net</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Project Updates</h4>","Support Services","","inherit","closed","open","","268-revision-v1","","","2014-10-06 11:40:46","2014-10-06 11:40:46","","268","http://inch-reform.codio.io:3000/wordpress/268-revision-v1/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("270","1","2014-10-06 11:43:16","2014-10-06 11:43:16","<h1 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Procurement</h1>\r\n<h3>Workstream Aim</h3>\r\n<p class=\"lead\">To identify the potential areas where collaboration…</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Project Aims</h3>\r\nTo deliver savings by reviewing demand for consumable products across the seven Trusts and using different procurement levers, depending on the supplier market, to reduce the unit cost paid.\r\n\r\nTo standardise the product usage across the region committing future demand to suppliers in return for a\r\ncost reduction.\r\n<h3>Project Benefits</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To deliver savings by reviewing demand for consumable products across the seven Trusts. Savings would be retained by each Trust for reinvestment in patient care.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Project Lead</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li><strong>Chief Executive Sponsors</strong>: Andrew Cash, Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Project Managers</strong> Jon Edwards - Jonathan.edwards@supplychain.nhs.uk, Jordan Hope Jordan.Hope@sth.nhs.uk</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Project Updates</h4>","Procurement","","publish","closed","open","","procurement","","","2014-10-06 11:43:16","2014-10-06 11:43:16","","16","http://inch-reform.codio.io:3000/wordpress/?page_id=270","0","page","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("271","1","2014-10-06 11:43:16","2014-10-06 11:43:16","<h1 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Procurement</h1>\r\n<h3>Workstream Aim</h3>\r\n<p class=\"lead\">To identify the potential areas where collaboration…</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Project Aims</h3>\r\nTo deliver savings by reviewing demand for consumable products across the seven Trusts and using different procurement levers, depending on the supplier market, to reduce the unit cost paid.\r\n\r\nTo standardise the product usage across the region committing future demand to suppliers in return for a\r\ncost reduction.\r\n<h3>Project Benefits</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To deliver savings by reviewing demand for consumable products across the seven Trusts. Savings would be retained by each Trust for reinvestment in patient care.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Project Lead</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\n	<li><strong>Chief Executive Sponsors</strong>: Andrew Cash, Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Project Managers</strong> Jon Edwards - Jonathan.edwards@supplychain.nhs.uk, Jordan Hope Jordan.Hope@sth.nhs.uk</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 class=\"sheffchildbrand workstream-h1 lighttext\">Project Updates</h4>","Procurement","","inherit","closed","open","","270-revision-v1","","","2014-10-06 11:43:16","2014-10-06 11:43:16","","270","http://inch-reform.codio.io:3000/wordpress/270-revision-v1/","0","revision","","0");
